I think it’s been pretty clear from the beginning of the coronavirus outbreak that President Trump’s top concern has been American business, rather than public health.
As CNBC reported:[I]nside the administration, some officials were stunned by Trump’s claim Monday that he would hold a press conference Tuesday to announce an economic plan.
He also proposed delaying the tax filing deadline and providing sick leave, along with a demand that the government “help” the travel industry and bail out the oil and gas industry.
Let us note that Trump’s family business, from which he has continued to profit throughout his presidency, is the hotel industry.
As usual, Donald Trump’s primary concern, if not his sole concern, is Donald Trump.